ce:section.ce:para:
We further investigated the feasibility to establish a paper-based sensor using the MoS2 QDs for fluazinam detection. After integrated with chitosan and MoS2 QDs, the paper-based sensor exhibited a strong blue fluorescence under the ultraviolet excitation (Fig. 7
                        A, Z0: the combination of 12 same blank zones). Upon the addition of fluazinam, clear fluorescence quenching of test zones was observed (Fig. 7B). Standard digital images (Fig. 7C and D) and RGB difference map (Fig. 7E) before and after response with fluazinam were automatically obtained from the IISV system designed by our lab. As shown in Fig. 7B, the fluorescent paper faded gradually with increasing concentration of fluzinam, which was consistent with the increasingly obvious color change in RGB difference map (Fig. 7E), realizing the nake-eyed analysis of fluzinam. In addition, the Euclidean distance (ED) of ΔRGB in every response pot was calculated and it exhibited a linear relationship with the logarithm of fluzinam concentration from 10 μM to 800 μM (Fig. 8
                        ). The regression equation could be described as: EDΔRGB = 33.62 lg CFA (mM) + 70.06 (R2 = 0.9722) with the limit of detection of 2.26 μM, realizing the digital readout of paper-based sensor for fluzinam detection. Those results indicated the proposed strategy provided a convenient and low-cost platform for in-field monitor of fluazinam.
